title: For Sale:  .22LR Jiminez JA-22
postcontent: .22LR Jiminez JA-22   6+1 Shot   "Ring-of-Fire" Handgun w/Two (2) 6-Round MagazinesEMAIL:   REDACTEDUp Front:   These little Handy-Dandy handguns are known as "Jammomatics", by both Those Who Like Them and Those Who Would Not Have One Under Any Circumstances.   I knew all this when I bought this one.   Still had to try it out.   JA-22s require (a) Breaking in, (b) "Fluffing and Buffing", and (c) a whole lot of messing around and tuning to get them to work.   Which is what I have been doing.  I bought this one at 13th Street Jewelry and Loan for around $120 out-the-door just from plain old curiosity and perversity, to see what-the-heck about such a controversial little handgun.   It has been a ton of fun and a lot of learning.   It's not totally jam-free yet, but it works a whole bunch better than when I first purchased it.The "feel" of this handgun is totally wicked.   So much power in such a small package, right in the palm of your hand.   Totally concealable.  Pocket perfect fit.   Seven blasting rounds of CCI Stingers, fast as you can pull the trigger.   And--full, complete disclosure:  Now and Then a Jam Here and There.   Has striker-fire operation, manual safety, and does NOT have a slide lock.   The JA-22 is surprisingly accurate for such a short-barreled handgun:   That's a good part of the Fun Part with this pistol.   It hits exactly where title: For Sale:  Kel Tec RFB 308 Rifle RFB18 TAN KelTec NEW FDE
postcontent: Description / Manufacturer Information:  RFB stands for Rifle, Forward-ejecting Bullpup. Why forward-ejecting? Because it allows the RFB to be the first truly ambidextrous 7.62 NATO Bullpup ever developed. The patented, dual-extractor system maintains control of the case from the moment it leaves the magazine and upon firing, pulls the fired case from the chamber and lifts them to push them into an ejection chute above the barrel, where they exit. The Bullpup configuration and tilting-block mechanism allow the 18" model to be only 26.1" long, or as much as 14" shorter in overall length than its competitors with equal barrel lengths. Furthermore, the stock and mechanism cross-section is similar to a conventional rifle, in stark contrast to existing Bullpup rifles. The RFB is also the safest Bullpup ever developed because the breech is separated from the shooters face by two layers of 1.6 mm steel. In the highly unlikely event of a case rupture, gas expansion is directed downwards through the magazine well to protect the shooters head and face. Manufacturer: KelTec Model: RFB Condition: NEW Caliber/Gauge: 308WIN
